      public SemanticVersion(@NotNull @NotNull String version)
      Creates a new SemanticVersion.
      Parameters:
      version - A version string in the semantic versioning format. E.g. "1.2.4". A pre-release or build metadata string can be added using a hyphen at the end of the string, e.g. "1.2.4-beta.1".

  • Method Details

    • compareTo

      public int compareTo(@NotNull @NotNull SemanticVersion other)
      Compares this version with another semantic version. If parsing failed with either this or other this will silently return 0.
      Specified by:
      compareTo in interface Comparable<SemanticVersion>
      Parameters:
      other - The other semantic version to compare against.
      Returns:
      1 if this is newer than other and -1 if other is newer. 0 if the same or parsing failed.
      Since:
      0.1.11

      public int hashCode()
